.note code { background:#f3f4f6; padding:2px 6px; border-radius:4px; }
</style>
</head>
<body>
<div class="wrap">
<h1>Stack DE sendable test</h1>
<p class="lead">Creates an Automation Triggered-style entry DE, shows sendable config, then tries repair variants for <strong>Used for sending</strong> and <strong>Relates to Subscriber On</strong>.</p>
%%[IF @showForm == "true" THEN]%%
<div class="card">
<form method="get" action="%%=RequestParameter('PAGEURL')=%%">
<input type="hidden" name="run" value="1">
<label for="deName">DE name</label>
<input type="text" id="deName" name="deName" placeholder="Test_Stack_DE_%%=Format(Now(),'yyyyMMdd_HHmmss')=%%" required>
<label for="customerKey">Customer key (optional — slug from name if blank)</label>
<input type="text" id="customerKey" name="customerKey" placeholder="Leave blank to derive from name">
<label for="mode">Mode</label>
<select id="mode" name="mode">
<option value="create">Create DE + auto-repair sendable</option>
<option value="repair">Repair sendable on existing DE</option>
<option value="inspect">Inspect sendable config only</option>
</select>
<button type="submit" class="btn-primary">Run test</button>
</form>
</div>
<div class="note">
<p><strong>Create</strong> uses the same eventDefinitions bootstrap as Automation Triggered, then tries these SOAP repair variants:</p>
<ul>
<li><code>working-quick-send</code> — email + _SubscriberKey + id (matches your working DE JSON)</li>
<li><code>automation-old-broken</code> — email + SubscriberKey + SubscriberKey (old code)</li>
</ul>
</div>
%%[ELSE]%%
<div class="card">
<div class="result">%%=v(@resultText)=%%</div>
<div style="margin-top:16px;">
<a class="btn btn-secondary" href="%%=RequestParameter('PAGEURL')=%%">Run another test</a>
</div>
</div>
%%[ENDIF]%%
</div>
</body>
</html>
